---
// How a phishing attack steals credentials, step by step.
---
<figure class="figure">
  <svg viewBox="0 0 450 210" role="img" aria-label="Phishing flow: attacker sends a fake lure, victim enters details on a fake site, credentials return to the attacker">
    <!-- attacker -->
    <rect x="20" y="80" width="80" height="44" rx="9" class="dgm-fill-accent"></rect>
    <text x="60" y="100" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-inv" font-size="11.5" font-weight="700">Attacker</text>
    <text x="60" y="115" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-inv" font-size="9">disguised as a bank</text>

    <!-- lure -->
    <line x1="100" y1="102" x2="185" y2="102" class="dgm-stroke-accent dgm-flow" stroke-width="2.2" marker-end="url(#ph-arrow)"></line>
    <text x="142" y="94" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-muted" font-size="9.5">① fake email /</text>
    <text x="142" y="118" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-muted" font-size="9.5">SMS lure</text>

    <!-- victim -->
    <rect x="190" y="80" width="80" height="44" rx="9" class="dgm-fill-surface dgm-stroke" stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
    <text x="230" y="100" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-text" font-size="11.5" font-weight="650">Victim</text>
    <text x="230" y="115" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-muted" font-size="9">clicks the link</text>

    <!-- to fake site -->
    <line x1="270" y1="102" x2="355" y2="102" class="dgm-stroke-accent dgm-flow" stroke-width="2.2" marker-end="url(#ph-arrow)"></line>
    <text x="312" y="94" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-muted" font-size="9.5">② enters</text>
    <text x="312" y="118" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-muted" font-size="9.5">password</text>

    <!-- fake site -->
    <rect x="360" y="80" width="80" height="44" rx="9" class="dgm-fill-surface dgm-stroke-danger" stroke-width="1.6"></rect>
    <text x="400" y="100" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-text" font-size="11" font-weight="650">Fake site</text>
    <text x="400" y="115" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-fill-danger" font-size="9">look-alike</text>

    <!-- credentials back to attacker -->
    <path d="M400 124 C400 175, 60 175, 60 128" fill="none" class="dgm-stroke-danger dgm-flow" stroke-width="2.2" marker-end="url(#ph-arrow-d)"></path>
    <text x="230" y="170" text-anchor="middle" class="dgm-fill-danger" font-size="10" font-weight="650">③ credentials stolen → fraud</text>

    <defs>
      <marker id="ph-arrow" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto">
        <path d="M0 0 L6 3 L0 6 z" class="dgm-fill-accent"></path>
      </marker>
      <marker id="ph-arrow-d" markerWidth="8" markerHeight="8" refX="6" refY="3" orient="auto">
        <path d="M0 0 L6 3 L0 6 z" class="dgm-fill-danger"></path>
      </marker>
    </defs>
  </svg>
  <figcaption>Phishing in three steps: a trusted-looking lure → a fake site that harvests details → the stolen credentials flow back to the attacker.</figcaption>
</figure>
